nounced by Naver in Korea ( https://www.kedglobal.com/tech,-media-telecom/n=
ewsView/ked202310300017 ). The economics there, I don=E2=80=99t now have to=
 port my application, you get good AI performance on the portion of the wor=
kload where you=E2=80=99re inferencing, but you have all the benefits of th=
e software ecosystem for the whole application.

But importantly, I think edge and client AI is governed by the three laws. =
The laws of economics: it is cheaper to do it on the client versus in the c=
loud. The laws of physics: it is faster to do it on the client versus round=
 tripping your data to the cloud. And the third is the laws of the land: do=
 I have data privacy? So for those three reasons, I believe there=E2=80=99s=
 all going to be this push to inferencing to the edge and to the client and=
 that=E2=80=99s where I think the action comes. That=E2=80=99s why Meteor L=
ake and the AIPC is something=E2=80=94

*Do you think though it=E2=80=99s competitive today or is this an issue whe=
re because Nvidia=E2=80=99s supply constraints, you have time and space to =
catch up such that you=E2=80=99re good enough by the time GPUs are cheap?*

*PG:* For the big high end, hey, Gaudi is a good chip today. I ran some of =
the ML performance benchmarks today versus H100s and A100s, we=E2=80=99re s=
tarting to show up.

*I have on my somewhat skeptical face, but continue.*

*PG:* Hey, they win a lot, I win some. It just means we are now starting to=
 show up and I=E2=80=99m a lot cheaper than that so I win the TCO at scale.

*You=E2=80=99re cheaper and you=E2=80=99re more available. So those are two=
 good advantages.*

*PG:* So availability, starting to get good performance, and certainly the =
market once an alternative is there, Xeon is going to be widely deployed, a=
nd they=E2=80=99re all going to be AI-enhanced. And then for client and edg=
e, Xeons at the edge are going to be very dominant. We have all of our Xeon=
 Ds ( https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/products/details/processors/x=
eon/d.html ) and those products, they=E2=80=99ll get AI-enhanced. And then =
Meteor Lake, Lunar Lake, Aerolake, Panther Lake, we have a very robust road=
map on the client side. So all of that taken together, AI is a workload and=
 we are going to make it available everywhere and that=E2=80=99s what our o=
verall strategy=E2=80=99s about. Compete at the high end, deliver it in Xeo=
n, but make it available at the client and edge.

*Well, it=E2=80=99s been a couple years since we talked. I have to say I=E2=
=80=99ve been pretty impressed by the progress, but in two years it=E2=80=
=99ll be very interesting to look back and I think by then we=E2=80=99ll se=
e did you make it or not?*

*PG:* Yeah. Did we make it happen? Hey, I said it was a five-year journey, =
we=E2=80=99re halfway through the journey and I feel like we=E2=80=99re ove=
r halfway done with the assignment.

